text.__SUMMARY__:
Acacia duriuscula is a shrub or tree of the genus Acacia and the subgenus Plurinerves. It is native to an area in the Wheatbelt and Goldfields-Esperance regions of Western Australia.

The erect resinous shrub or tree typically grows to a height of 0.7 to 3 metres (2 to 10 ft). It blooms from July to October and produces yellow flowers.
